title: Pocahontas Disney Unfinished Workprint 1995
description:
Here is a workprint, taken from VHS, of an early, unfinished version of Disney's 1995 film Pocahontas.

   The script is finalized at this point, and there are few differences from the final film. However, animation is still in progress and much of the film is still in pencil test - very beautiful pencil tests, at that! There are also a lot of storyboards.

   "Mine Mine Mine" has its original (much better) ending here, where the forest has been utterly devastated by Radcliffe's men, and looks like a bomb hit it. The deleted love song "If I Never Knew You" is also here.


   This appears to have been animator Glen Keane's own VHS copy at some point.
